---
import { ArrowUpRight, ExternalLink } from "@lucide/astro";
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { links } from "../../../data/site.js";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="BCP and Credicorp product leadership | Kevin Astuhuaman"
  description="Kevin Astuhuaman's six-year product progression across SMB lending, marketplace, growth, and platform work at BCP and Credicorp."
  path="/projects/smb-fintech-bcp-credicorp/"
  pageType="article"
  about="SMB fintech product leadership"
>
  <header class="page-hero bcp-hero">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Regulated product leadership | 2018-2024</p>
      <h1>Six years turning SMB financial friction into production products.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        I progressed from Product Analyst to Lead Product Manager at BCP/Credicorp, leading lending, marketplace, pricing, growth, and platform work in Peru's largest bank.
      </p>
      <div class="case-meta">
        <span><strong>Progression:</strong> Analyst -> PM -> Senior PM -> Lead PM</span>
        <span><strong>Leadership:</strong> 9 product direct reports</span>
        <span><strong>Partners:</strong> Risk, compliance, engineering, design, analytics, commercial</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="article-shell">
    <p class="eyebrow">The operating context</p>
    <h2>Small businesses needed speed. The bank needed risk discipline.</h2>
    <p>
      The product work sat between customers who could not wait a week for working capital and a regulated institution that needed reliable identity, risk, pricing, compliance, and distribution. Shipping a cleaner funnel was useful only when the underlying decision and operating model could support it.
    </p>

    <section class="progression" aria-labelledby="progression-title">
      <h3 id="progression-title">Product progression</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><span>Product Analyst</span><strong>Found opportunity through customer and portfolio data</strong></li>
        <li><span>Product Manager</span><strong>Owned launches, funnels, experiments, and partnerships</strong></li>
        <li><span>Senior Product Manager</span><strong>Led cross-product architecture and market growth</strong></li>
        <li><span>Lead Product Manager</span><strong>Managed product leaders, P&amp;L decisions, and enterprise alignment</strong></li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <h2>Three products show the range.</h2>

    <section class="bcp-story">
      <div class="story-number">01</div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">SMB marketplace</p>
        <h3>Build one place where lending, insurance, and payments reinforce each other.</h3>
        <p>
          I launched and scaled Peru's first SMB digital marketplace by integrating services, improving the API structure, and refining the customer journey. The product reached 180K monthly active users and increased product cross-sell per client by 28%.
        </p>
        <div class="story-metrics"><strong>180K MAU</strong><strong>+28% cross-sell</strong></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bcp-story">
      <div class="story-number">02</div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Personalized lending</p>
        <h3>Move the credit decision from a seven-day process to an immediate answer.</h3>
        <p>
          I led customer research, roadmap definition, pilot, and launch for a personalized loan with automated approval and dynamic rates. The product reduced processing from seven days to immediate approval and generated $40M in nine months.
        </p>
        <div class="story-metrics"><strong>7 days -> immediate</strong><strong>$40M in 9 months</strong></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bcp-story">
      <div class="story-number">03</div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Pricing and conversion</p>
        <h3>Use risk-based pricing as a product experiment, not a static policy.</h3>
        <p>
          I devised an ML-driven pricing strategy for recurring clients and tested it through controlled experiments. Conversion increased 32%, and the product reached 19.6% market share in seven months.
        </p>
        <div class="story-metrics"><strong>+32% conversion</strong><strong>19.6% market share</strong></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <h2>The operating model behind the outcomes</h2>
    <figure class="ecosystem-artifact" aria-labelledby="ecosystem-title">
      <figcaption id="ecosystem-title">Public-safe reconstruction of the product operating system</figcaption>
      <div class="customer-core">SMB customer decision</div>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Customer evidence</strong><span>50+ interviews and journey analysis</span></li>
        <li><strong>Risk and pricing</strong><span>Automated evaluation and controlled experiments</span></li>
        <li><strong>Product platform</strong><span>Data, identity, APIs, and shared architecture</span></li>
        <li><strong>Distribution</strong><span>Mobile, marketplace, and 12M+ user wallet partners</span></li>
        <li><strong>Operation</strong><span>Compliance, availability, performance, and P&amp;L</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p>The artifact is reconstructed from public resume content and contains no internal bank architecture.</p>
    </figure>

    <h2>What senior ownership looked like</h2>
    <dl class="decision-list">
      <div class="decision">
        <dt>Decide across constraints</dt>
        <dd>Product choices had to work for customers, risk, compliance, engineering capacity, pricing, and commercial distribution at the same time.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="decision">
        <dt>Lead through other product managers</dt>
        <dd>As Lead Product Manager, I directed nine product reports and aligned cross-functional teams around availability, growth, and customer-segment decisions.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="decision">
        <dt>Connect platform to outcome</dt>
        <dd>The shared data, identity, and risk architecture mattered because it enabled faster product launches, 26% year-over-year sales growth, and sixfold website traffic.</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <h2>Why this matters for AI product work</h2>
    <p>
      AI products still need distribution, incentives, guardrails, experimentation, and an operating owner. BCP taught me to evaluate a system by the customer and business decisions it improves, especially when an incorrect decision has real financial and regulatory consequences.
    </p>

    <div class="button-row final-actions">
      <a class="button button-dark" href="/resume/">View the full chronology <ArrowUpRight aria-hidden="true" size={17} /></a>
      <a class="button" href={links.publicProfile}>Public PUCP profile <ExternalLink aria-hidden="true" size={16} /></a>
      <a class="button" href="/contact/">Contact Kevin</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .bcp-hero {
    background: #075f48;
  }

  .progression {
    margin: 50px 0 72px;
    padding: clamp(24px, 4vw, 40px);
    background: #0c6d52;
    color: white;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .progression ol {
    margin: 26px 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .progression li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 190px 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    padding: 18px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  }

  .progression li span {
    color: #bfe7d9;
  }

  .bcp-story {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 90px 1fr;
    gap: 34px;
    padding: 48px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #d7d7d0;
  }

  .story-number {
    color: #087858;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .bcp-story h3 {
    max-width: 680px;
    font-size: 2.55rem;
  }

  .bcp-story p:not(.eyebrow) {
    max-width: 680px;
    color: #44443f;
  }

  .story-metrics {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px;
    margin-top: 24px;
  }

  .story-metrics strong {
    padding: 9px 11px;
    background: #dff2ea;
    color: #075f48;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
  }

  .ecosystem-artifact {
    margin: 48px 0;
    padding: clamp(24px, 4vw, 42px);
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #d7d7d0;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .ecosystem-artifact figcaption {
    margin-bottom: 26px;
    font-weight: 720;
  }

  .customer-core {
    padding: 22px;
    background: #075f48;
    color: white;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 740;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .ecosystem-artifact ul {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    margin: 14px 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .ecosystem-artifact li {
    padding: 18px 12px;
    border-right: 1px solid #d7d7d0;
  }

  .ecosystem-artifact li:last-child {
    border-right: 0;
  }

  .ecosystem-artifact li strong,
  .ecosystem-artifact li span {
    display: block;
  }

  .ecosystem-artifact li span {
    margin-top: 8px;
    color: #666660;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }

  .ecosystem-artifact > p {
    margin: 20px 0 0;
    color: #666660;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }

  .final-actions {
    margin-top: 56px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .bcp-story h3 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    .progression li,
    .bcp-story {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 10px;
    }

    .ecosystem-artifact ul {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .ecosystem-artifact li {
      border-right: 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #d7d7d0;
    }
  }
</style>
